CatDescriptText: Mrs. Susie Williams, housewife, Homewood and Mr. Frank Greenwall, Hill District, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1962, pg. 12 with question: "How do you think the Pirates will do in 1962?" Mrs. Susie Williams' answer reads: "I don't know too much about baseball, but they will probably do all right.  They may end up in the top half."  Mr. Frank Greenwall's answer reads: "No good.  Second division all the way for them."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Susie Williams wearing light colored head scarf, eyeglasses, striped top, and light colored overcoat, posed in front of light colored building; Portrait of Frank Greenwall wearing brushed up hairstyle and jacket with pointed pocket flaps, posed in front of building with chiseled block trim
